						               													<description>On a remote island, labeled &amp;quot;cursed&amp;quot; to ward off curious eyes, six exemplary people have been summoned against their will to fight against each other in the colosseum. None may leave until a Champion is chosen.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In Spellbound Champions you take the part of one of these six characters to compete as:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Vogak, the Steadfast Orc Warrior&amp;#10;Aurora, the Enchanting Human Magi&amp;#10;Cyrid, the Auspicious Goblin Gambler&amp;#10;Lavanna, the Agile Elf Ranger&amp;#10;Rosie, the Entertaining Halfing Bard&amp;#10;Baeddan, the Virtuous Dwarf Cleric&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In a kill or be killed environment, you must push yourself to the limits, or hope you're equipped enough to survive a fight to the death.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;Spellbound Champions&amp;quot; is a player versus player role-playing game for 2-6 players that takes about an hour to play. Try Free-For-All, teams, or take on your nemesis 1 on 1.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each character has a pre-constructed deck of 60 cards they must use to defeat their opponents. 3 types of action cards are in place: Whenever, Combat, and Ability. Abilities may only be used on your turn, while Whenever cards have no limit on them. Combat cards have a limit of 1 card on your turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Last player alive is the winner, unless on a team, in which the team is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
